******
[1] Gadsden County: horse, goat
Date: Tue 14 Jul 2015
Source: Tallahassee Democrat [edited]
http://www.tallahassee.com/story/news/2015/07/14/animals-in-gadsden-test-positive-for-eee/30133983/


A goat and a horse tested positive in Gadsden County [Florida] for eastern equine encephalitis last week [week of 6 Jul 2015] and health officials are linking it to an increase in mosquito activity. That increase in activity puts humans more at risk as the Florida Health Department in Gadsden County and county mosquito control monitor the insect's numbers and the prevalence of the virus.

No cases have been reported in Leon or Wakulla counties, but in 2015, positive samples have been taken from 38 sentinel chickens, 14 horses, and one goat across 19 counties, according to DOH records.

Officials are warning to take precautions to avoid being bitten.

Ways to reduce exposure to mosquitoes:
- drain standing water to stop mosquitoes from breeding;
- cover skin with long pants and long-sleeve shirts and apply repellent to exposed skin

[Byline: Karl Etters]

