[The state of can be located on the HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3512991,212. For a map of the state, see http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/united_states/florida_90.jpg Polk County is in central Florida and Gadsden County is at the western end of the border with Georgia.

Unfortunately, EEE is enzootic in Florida and outbreaks, whether in animals or humans, are not unexpected. Thus, the need to take precautions, at least until you have developed a protective titre, and make sure your horses are vaccinated annually. - Mod.MHJ]
